5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221951%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFlaco%2C%20a%20Eurasian%20eagle%20owl%20that%20escaped%20from%20the%20Central%20Park%20Zoo.%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Lichtenstein%2FCorbis%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFlaco%2C%20the%20loose%20Central%20Park%20Zoo%20owl%2C%20died%20with%20lethal%20levels%20of%20rat%20poison%20%C2%A0in%20his%20system.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERodenticides%20used%20in%20cities%20like%20New%20York%20also%20poison%20other%20wildlife%2C%20especially%20birds%20of%20prey.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20problem%20could%20become%20worse%20as%20cities%20ramp%20up%20their%20efforts%20to%20combat%20rats.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFlaco%2C%20the%20owl%20who%20escaped%20from%20the%20Central%20Park%20Zoo%20last%20year%20and%20transitioned%20to%20life%20as%20a%20free%20New%20Yorker%2C%20had%20lethal%20levels%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-new-rat-killing-method-highly-successful-expanding-new-areas-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erat%20poison%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20his%20system%20when%20he%20died%20last%20month%20%E2%80%94%20a%20problem%20that%20impacts%20non-famous%20birds%20of%20prey%20and%20other%20animals%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEurasian%20eagle-owl%20got%20loose%20in%20February%202023%3B%20the%20mesh%20of%20his%20enclosure%20was%20found%20tampered%20with.%20Police%20have%20said%20the%20investigation%20is%20ongoing%2C%20but%20no%20information%20about%20potential%20suspects%20has%20been%20released.%20After%20over%20a%20year%20flying%20wild%2C%20Flaco%20collided%20with%20a%20building%20on%20the%20Upper%20West%20Side%20and%20died%20on%20February%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.wcs.org%2FNews-Releases%2FarticleType%2FArticleView%2FarticleId%2F22247%2FCentral-Park-Zoo-Releases-Postmortem-Testing-Results-for-Flaco-the-Eurasian-Eagle-Owl.aspx%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECentral%20Park%20Zoo%3C%2Fa%3E%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20Monday%20the%20necropsy%20showed%20Flaco%20had%20two%20underlying%20conditions%3A%20severe%20pigeon%20virus%2C%20from%20preying%20on%20Manhattan%20pigeons%2C%20and%20exposure%20to%20four%20different%20kinds%20of%20rat%20poison%20that%20the%20city%20employs%20to%20combat%20its%20rodent%20problem.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20factors%20would%20have%20been%20debilitating%20and%20ultimately%20fatal%2C%20even%20without%20a%20traumatic%20injury%2C%20and%20may%20have%20predisposed%20him%20to%20flying%20into%20or%20falling%20from%20the%20building%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20zoo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20zoo%20noted%20the%20contributing%20factors%20that%20caused%20Flaco's%20early%20death%20%26quot%3Bunderscore%20the%20hazards%20faced%20by%20wild%20birds%2C%20especially%20in%20an%20urban%20setting.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20many%20birds%20and%20other%20wildlife%20are%20regularly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnyc-has-rat-czar-could-chicago-and-boston-be-next-2023-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epoisoned%20by%20rodenticides%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20are%20meant%20for%20rats%20%E2%80%94%20an%20occurrence%20that%20could%20become%20increasingly%20likely%20as%20cities%20like%20New%20York%2C%20Chicago%2C%20and%20Boston%20up%20the%20ante%20on%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-cities-can-not-get-rid-of-rats-2018-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erat-fighting%20efforts%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnticoagulant%20rodenticides%20%E2%80%94%20which%20prevent%20blood%20from%20clotting%20and%20cause%20animals%20to%20bleed%20to%20death%20internally%20%E2%80%94%20used%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frattiest-cities-in-the-us-america-pest-control-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etarget%20rats%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20inadvertently%20poisoned%20other%20species%20worldwide%2C%20with%20birds%20of%20prey%20being%20most%20impacted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202018%20literature%20review%20published%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC6395208%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJournal%20of%20Veterinary%20Medical%20Science%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20rat%20poison%20was%20detected%20in%2060%25%20of%20various%20raptor%20species%20globally%2C%20which%20can%20include%20owls%2C%20falcons%2C%20hawks%2C%20and%20eagles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20birds%20can%20be%20exposed%20to%20rat%20poison%20in%20several%20ways%3A%20by%20directly%20coming%20into%20contact%20with%20it%20or%20by%20eating%20poisoned%20prey%2C%20which%20could%20be%20rats%20or%20mice%2C%20or%20even%20a%20non-rodent%20species%2C%20like%20small%20mammals%20and%20reptiles%2C%20that%20were%20also%20unintentionally%20exposed%20to%20it.%20Because%20the%20rat%20poison%20does%20not%20kill%20the%20animal%20for%20several%20days%2C%20there's%20time%20for%20an%20owl%20to%20prey%20on%20it%20and%20also%20injest%20the%20poison.%20Even%20once%20the%20animals%20are%20dead%2C%20they%20still%20maintain%20levels%20of%20poison%20that%20can%20transfer%20to%20scavengers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202020%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsetac.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1002%2Fetc.4853%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20authored%20by%20Maureen%20Murray%2C%20director%20of%20Tufts%20Wildlife%20Clinic%20in%20Massachusetts%2C%20found%20that%20100%25%20of%20the%2043%20red-tailed%20hawks%20sampled%20at%20the%20clinic%20between%202017%20and%202019%20had%20been%20exposed%20to%20rat%20poison.%20Murray%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnow.tufts.edu%2F2020%2F09%2F16%2Funderstanding-risks-rodent-poisons-birds-prey%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETufts%20Now%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20numbers%20of%20raptors%20with%20rat%20poison%20seen%20by%20the%20clinic%20had%20steadily%20increased.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20ability%20of%20these%20rodenticides%20to%20permeate%20the%20food%20chain%20and%20ecosystems%20is%20pretty%20remarkable%2C%26quot%3B%20Murray%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BRed-tailed%20hawks%20eat%20a%20lot%20of%20small%20mammals%2C%20but%20they%20also%20eat%20birds%2C%20reptiles%2C%20or%20amphibians%3B%20they%20might%20scavenge.%20Ultimately%2C%20their%20prey%20base%20is%20very%20contaminated.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ace-eco.org%2Fvol13%2Fiss1%2Fart2%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%202018%20conducted%20in%20California%20found%2070%25%20of%20northern%20spotted%20owls%2C%20a%20protected%20threatened%20species%20under%20the%20Endangered%20Species%20Act%2C%20tested%20positive%20for%20rat%20poison%2C%20while%2040%25%20of%20barred%20owls%20tested%20positive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20poisoning%20is%20not%20just%20an%20issue%20for%20birds%20of%20prey.%20A%202018%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.biologicaldiversity.org%2Fnews%2Fpress_releases%2F2018%2Frat-poison-12-12-2018.php%23%3A~%3Atext%3DSACRAMENTO%252C%2520Calif.%2Cor%2520ban%2520the%2520powerful%2520toxins.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20California%20Department%20of%20Pesticide%20Regulation%20found%2085%25%20of%20mountain%20lions%2C%20bobcats%2C%20and%20fishers%20that%20were%20tested%20had%20been%20poisoned%20by%20rodenticides.%20Raccoons%2C%20foxes%2C%20skunks%2C%20coyotes%2C%20and%20house%20pets%20can%20also%20be%20exposed%20to%20rat%20poison%2C%20according%20to%20the%20California%20Department%20of%20Fish%20and%20Wildlife.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20cities%20are%20amping%20up%20the%20use%20of%20rat%20poison%2C%20others%20are%20addressing%20the%20threat%20posed%20to%20wildlife.%20The%20use%20of%20rat%20poison%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwildlife.ca.gov%2FLiving-with-Wildlife%2FRodenticides%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erestricted%20in%20California%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20years%2C%20though%20the%20rodenticides%20continued%20to%20show%20up%20in%20animals%20that%20were%20not%20being%20targeted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20October%2C%20Gov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%20signed%20a%20bill%20expanding%20the%20moratorium%20on%20certain%20rat%20poisons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20really%20needed%20these%20protections%20to%20ease%20the%20needless%20suffering%20of%20pumas%2C%20foxes%20and%20owls%2C%26quot%3B%20Tiffany%20Yap%2C%20a%20senior%20scientist%20at%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbiologicaldiversity.org%2Fw%2Fnews%2Fpress-releases%2Fcalifornia-expands-toxic-rat-poison-ban-2023-10-13%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520California%2520Ecosystems%2520Protection%2520Act%2Cstill%2520on%2520the%2520market%2520today.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECenter%20for%20Biological%20Diversity%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release%2C%20adding%3A%20%26quot%3BRat%20poison%20indiscriminately%20harms%20animals%20up%20and%20down%20the%20food%20chain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflaco-the-owl-death-risk-rat-poison-wildlife-cities-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711586273000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66049c933f923f7dab01e6c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflaco-the-owl-death-risk-rat-poison-wildlife-cities-2024-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Flaco%20the%20owl%20had%20lethal%20levels%20of%20rat%20poison%20in%20his%20system.%20Rodenticides%20often%20poison%20birds%20of%20prey%20as%20well%20as%20mountain%20lions%2C%20bobcats%2C%20and%20fishers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kvlamis%40insider.com%20(Kelsey%20Vlamis)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A368%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fflaco-the-owl-death-risk-rat-poison-wildlife-cities-2024-3%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Biden%20administration%20to%20lend%20%241.5%20billion%20for%20Michigan%20