2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFormer%20US%20Sen.%20Joe%20Lieberman%20died%20Wednesday.%20He%20was%2082.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ELieberman%20died%20in%20New%20York%20City%20due%20to%20complications%20from%20a%20fall%2C%20a%20statement%20from%20his%20family%20said.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20was%20the%20first%20Jewish%20candidate%20on%20a%20major%20party's%20presidential%20ticket%20and%20would%20have%20been%20the%20first%20Jewish%20VP.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20US%20Sen.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Fhub%2Fjoe-lieberman%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EJoe%20Lieberman%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Connecticut%2C%20who%20nearly%20won%20the%20vice%20presidency%20on%20the%20Democratic%20ticket%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Fhub%2Fal-gore%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAl%20Gore%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20disputed%202000%20election%20and%20who%20almost%20became%20Republican%20John%20McCain's%20running%20mate%20eight%20years%20later%2C%20has%20died%2C%20according%20to%20a%20statement%20issued%20by%20his%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman%20died%20in%20New%20York%20City%20on%20Wednesday%20due%20to%20complications%20from%20a%20fall%2C%20the%20statement%20said.%20He%20was%2082.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Democrat-turned-independent%20was%20never%20shy%20about%20veering%20from%20the%20party%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman's%20independent%20streak%20and%20especially%20his%20needling%20of%20Democratic%20presidential%20nominee%20Barack%20Obama%20during%20the%202008%20presidential%20contest%20rankled%20many%20Democrats%2C%20the%20party%20he%20aligned%20with%20in%20the%20Senate.%20Yet%20his%20support%20for%20gay%20rights%2C%20civil%20rights%2C%20abortion%20rights%20and%20environmental%20causes%20at%20times%20won%20him%20the%20praise%20of%20many%20liberals%20over%20the%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman%20came%20tantalizingly%20close%20to%20winning%20the%20vice%20presidency%20in%20the%20contentious%202000%20presidential%20contest%20that%20was%20decided%20by%20a%20537-vote%20margin%20victory%20for%20George%20W.%20Bush%20in%20Florida%20after%20a%20drawn-out%20recount%2C%20legal%20challenges%20and%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20decision.%20He%20was%20the%20first%20Jewish%20candidate%20on%20a%20major%20party's%20presidential%20ticket%20and%20would%20have%20been%20the%20first%20Jewish%20vice%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20also%20the%20first%20national%20Democrat%20to%20publicly%20criticize%20President%20Bill%20Clinton%20for%20his%20extramarital%20affair%20with%20a%20White%20House%20intern.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman%20sought%20the%20Democratic%20presidential%20nomination%20in%202004%20but%20dropped%20out%20after%20a%20weak%20showing%20in%20the%20early%20primaries.%20Four%20years%20later%2C%20he%20was%20an%20independent%20who%20was%20nearly%20chosen%20to%20be%20McCain's%20running%20mate.%20He%20and%20McCain%20were%20close%20pals%20who%20shared%20hawkish%20views%20on%20military%20and%20national%20security%20matters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcCain%20was%20leaning%20strongly%20toward%20choosing%20Lieberman%20for%20the%20ticket%20as%20the%202008%20GOP%20convention%20neared%2C%20but%20he%20chose%20Sarah%20Palin%20at%20the%20last%20minute%20after%20%26quot%3Bferocious%26quot%3B%20blowback%20from%20conservatives%20over%20Lieberman's%20liberal%20record%2C%20according%20to%20Steve%20Schmidt%2C%20who%20managed%20McCain's%20campaign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman%20generated%20controversy%20in%201998%20when%20he%20scolded%20Clinton%2C%20his%20friend%20of%20many%20years%2C%20for%20%26quot%3Bdisgraceful%20behavior%26quot%3B%20in%20an%20explosive%20speech%20on%20the%20Senate%20floor%20during%20the%20height%20of%20the%20scandal%20over%20his%20relationship%20with%20Monica%20Lewinsky.%20Yet%20Lieberman%20later%20voted%20against%20the%20impeachment%20of%20Clinton.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20defended%20his%20partisan%20switches%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20conscience%2C%20saying%20he%20always%20had%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20Connecticut%20voters%20at%20heart.%20Critics%20accused%20him%20of%20pursuing%20narrow%20self-interest%20and%20political%20expediency.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20announcing%20his%20retirement%20from%20the%20Senate%20in%202013%2C%20Lieberman%20acknowledged%20that%20he%20did%20%26quot%3Bnot%20always%20fit%20comfortably%20into%20conventional%20political%20boxes%26quot%3B%20and%20felt%20his%20first%20responsibility%20was%20to%20serve%20his%20constituents%2C%20state%20and%20country%2C%20not%20his%20political%20party.%20He%20had%20a%20tortured%20relationship%20with%20Democrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20final%20Senate%20speech%2C%20Lieberman%20urged%20Congress%20to%20look%20beyond%20party%20lines%20and%20partisan%20rancor%20to%20break%20Washington%20gridlock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20requires%20reaching%20across%20the%20aisle%20and%20finding%20partners%20from%20the%20opposite%20party%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lieberman.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20what%20is%20desperately%20needed%20in%20Washington%20now.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarry%20Reid%2C%20who%20served%20as%20Senate%20Democratic%20leader%2C%20once%20said%20that%20while%20he%20didn't%20always%20agree%20with%20the%20independent-minded%20Lieberman%2C%20he%20respected%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRegardless%20of%20our%20differences%2C%20I%20have%20never%20doubted%20Joe%20Lieberman's%20principles%20or%20his%20patriotism%2C%26quot%3B%20Reid%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20respect%20his%20independent%20streak%2C%20as%20it%20stems%20from%20strong%20convictions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrivately%2C%20some%20Democrats%20were%20often%20less%20charitable%20about%20Lieberman's%20forays%20across%20party%20lines%2C%20which%20they%20saw%20as%20disloyal.%20He%20bolted%20his%20party%20and%20turned%20independent%20after%20a%202006%20Senate%20primary%20loss%20in%20Connecticut.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman's%20strong%20support%20of%20the%20Iraq%20War%20hurt%20his%20statewide%20popularity.%20Democrats%20rejected%20Lieberman%20and%20handed%20the%202006%20primary%20to%20a%20political%20newcomer%20and%20an%20anti-war%20candidate%2C%20Ned%20Lamont.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDefying%20Democratic%20leaders%20and%20friends%2C%20Lieberman%20ran%20successfully%20for%20reelection%20as%20an%20independent%20and%20drew%20support%20from%20some%20Republican%20allies.%20Lieberman%20won%20praise%20from%20the%20White%20House%20and%20fundraising%20help%20from%20prominent%20Republicans%2C%20such%20as%20then-New%20York%20Mayor%20Mike%20Bloomberg%2C%20who%20himself%20later%20ran%20as%20an%20independent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman%20made%20his%20Senate%20experience%20and%20congressional%20clout%20a%20strong%20selling%20point%2C%20saying%20he'd%20fight%20hard%20for%20the%20state's%20defense%20jobs%20and%20its%20fair%20share%20of%20federal%20largesse.%20The%20strategy%20paid%20off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman%20won%20reelection%20to%20a%20fourth%20term%2C%20even%20though%20many%20of%20his%20Democratic%20allies%20and%20longtime%20friends%2C%20including%20former%20Sen.%20Chris%20Dodd%2C%20supported%20Lamont.%20Lieberman%20was%20candid%20about%20what%20he%20considered%20a%20betrayal%20by%20old%20pals%20such%20as%20Dodd%2C%20but%20the%20two%20men%20later%20reconciled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20his%20rebound%20reelection%20in%202006%2C%20Lieberman%20decided%20to%20caucus%20with%20Democrats%20in%20the%20Senate%2C%20who%20let%20him%20head%20a%20committee%20in%20return%20because%20they%20needed%20his%20vote%20to%20help%20keep%20control%20of%20the%20closely%20divided%20chamber.%20But%20it%20wasn't%20long%20until%20Lieberman%20was%20showing%20his%20independent%20streak%20and%20ruffling%20his%20Democratic%20caucus%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20decision%20of%20Democrats%20to%20let%20him%20join%20their%20caucus%20as%20an%20independent%2C%20Lieberman%20was%20an%20enthusiastic%20backer%20of%20McCain%20in%20the%202008%20presidential%20contest.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman's%20speech%20at%20the%202008%20GOP%20presidential%20nominating%20convention%20criticizing%20Obama%2C%20the%20Democratic%20presidential%20nominee%2C%20struck%20a%20deep%20nerve%20with%20many%20Democrats.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman%20cast%20Obama%20as%20a%20political%20show%20horse%2C%20a%20lightweight%20with%20a%20thin%20record%20of%20accomplishment%20in%20the%20Senate%20despite%20his%20soaring%20eloquence%20as%20a%20speaker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20Senate%2C%20during%20the%203%201%2F2%20years%20that%20Sen.%20Obama%20has%20been%20a%20member%2C%20he%20has%20not%20reached%20across%20party%20lines%20to%20...%20accomplish%20anything%20significant%2C%20nor%20has%20he%20been%20willing%20to%20take%20on%20powerful%20interest%20groups%20in%20the%20Democratic%20Party%20to%20get%20something%20done%2C%26quot%3B%20Lieberman%20said%20at%20the%20convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEloquence%20is%20no%20substitute%20for%20a%20record%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman%20campaigned%20heartily%20across%20the%20country%20for%20McCain.%20Many%20Democrats%20considered%20it%20a%20betrayal%20to%20Obama%20and%20his%20former%20party%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJoe%20Lieberman%20has%20said%20things%20that%20are%20totally%20irresponsible%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20Barack%20Obama%2C%26quot%3B%20House%20Democratic%20leader%20Nancy%20Pelosi%20of%20California%20said%20in%20a%20radio%20interview%20during%20the%202008%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20election%2C%20there%20was%20speculation%20Senate%20Democrats%20might%20strip%20Lieberman%20of%20his%20chairmanship%20of%20the%20Senate%20Homeland%20Security%20and%20Governmental%20Affairs%20Committee%20as%20payback.%20Sen.%20Patrick%20Leahy%2C%20D-Vt.%2C%20chair%20of%20the%20Judiciary%20Committee%2C%20was%20among%20those%20who%20said%20Lieberman%20should%20lose%20his%20chairmanship.%20Leahy%20branded%20Lieberman's%20attacks%20on%20Obama%20as%20%26quot%3Bbeyond%20the%20pale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20at%20Obama's%20urging%2C%20Senate%20Democrats%20decided%20not%20to%20punish%20Lieberman%20for%20supporting%20McCain%20and%20the%20GOP%20ticket.%20Obama%20was%20eager%20to%20strike%20a%20bipartisan%20tone%20for%20his%20presidency%20and%20giving%20Lieberman%20a%20pass%20helped%20reinforce%20that%20message.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%2C%20Vermont%20Sen.%20Bernie%20Sanders%2C%20an%20independent%20and%20staunch%20liberal%2C%20called%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bslap%20in%20the%20face%26quot%3B%20for%20millions%20of%20Americans%20who%20backed%20Obama.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman%20was%20known%20in%20the%20Senate%20for%20his%20hawkish%20foreign%20policy%20views%2C%20his%20pro-defense%20bent%20and%20his%20strong%20support%20for%20environmental%20causes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFive%20weeks%20after%20the%20Sept.%2011%2C%202001%2C%20attacks%2C%20he%20became%20one%20of%20the%20first%20politicians%20to%20call%20for%20the%20ouster%20of%20Iraqi%20leader%20Saddam%20Hussein%20and%20later%20voted%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20military%20invasion%20of%20Iraq.%20His%20vocal%20support%20for%20the%20war%20would%20later%20help%20doom%20his%20candidacy%20in%20the%202006%20Connecticut%20Democratic%20primary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman%20tended%20to%20vote%20with%20Democrats%20on%20most%20issues%20and%20was%20a%20longtime%20supporter%20of%20abortion%20rights%2C%20a%20stance%20that%20would%20have%20proved%20problematic%20with%20conservatives%20had%20McCain%20chosen%20him%20as%20his%20running%20mate%20in%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20played%20a%20key%20role%20in%20the%20legislation%20that%20created%20the%20Department%20of%20Homeland%20Security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELieberman%20grew%20up%20in%20Stamford%2C%20Connecticut%2C%20where%20his%20father%20ran%20a%20liquor%20store.%20Lieberman%20graduated%20from%20Yale%20University%20and%20Yale%20Law%20School%20in%20New%20Haven%20As%20Connecticut's%20attorney%20general%20from%201983%20to%201988%2C%20he%20was%20a%20strong%20consumer%20and%20environmental%20advocate.%20Lieberman%20vaulted%20into%20the%20Senate%20by%20defeating%20moderate%20Republican%20incumbent%2