%3E%2C%20including%20the%20dreadful%202022%20fires.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20a%20large%20cover%20of%20Chir%20Pine%20trees%20that%20are%20rich%20in%20organic%20polymers.%20This%20makes%20them%20easy%20to%20catch%20fire%20and%20hence%20vulnerable%20to%20forest%20fires%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20points%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20%3Cem%3EForest%20Survey%20of%20India%202019%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20forest%20cover%20in%20Uttarakhand%20is%2024%2C303.04%20sq%20km%2C%20which%20is%2045.44%20percent%20of%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20geographical%20area.%20And%20of%20the%20total%20forest%20cover%2C%20more%20than%20one-third%20(32.75%20percent)%20is%20prone%20to%20forest%20fires.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fforest-fire-1-1711027591.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pritam%20requests%20local%20people%20in%20the%20fire-prone%20regions%20to%20step%20up%20and%20respond%20to%20emergencies.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fforest-fire-1-1711027591.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fforest-fire-1-1711027591-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fforest-fire-1-1711027591-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fforest-fire-1-1711027591-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fforest-fire-1-1711027591-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-345479%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EPritam%20requests%20local%20people%20in%20the%20fire-prone%20regions%20to%20step%20up%20and%20respond%20to%20emergencies.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHighlighting%20the%20reasons%20that%20cause%20forest%20fires%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CIncidences%20of%20forest%20fires%20are%20common%20between%20February%20and%20mid-July.%20These%20fires%20are%20exacerbated%20largely%20by%20human%20activities%20such%20as%20slash-and-burn%20agriculture%2C%20the%20use%20of%20fire%20for%20land%20clearance%2C%20and%20reckless%20disposal%20of%20lit%20%3Cem%3Ebeedi%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20cigarettes.%20Besides%2C%20there%20is%20also%20a%20myth%20among%20local%20villagers%20that%20if%20they%20set%20the%20forest%20ablaze%2C%20it%20induces%20rain%20that%20will%20yield%20nutritious%20fodder%20for%20livestock.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThese%20fires%20not%20only%20result%20in%20the%20loss%20of%20valuable%20forest%20resources%20and%20wildlife%20but%20also%20affect%20humans%20in%20direct%20and%20indirect%20ways.%20It%20pollutes%20our%20water%20sources%20that%20originate%20from%20forests.%20It%20also%20increases%20their%20risk%20of%20drying%20up.%20Usually%2C%20villagers%20store%20firewood%20and%20fodder%20in%20their%20homes.%20And%20when%20these%20forest%20fires%20reach%20these%20habitations%2C%20they%20take%20a%20dreadful%20form%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20to%20be%20noted%20that%20Uttarakhand%20accounts%20for%201.6%20percent%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20total%20geographical%20area.%20But%20in%20terms%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F250621%2Fforest-fires-save-pradeep-mirase-ifs-similipal-malkangiri-environment-biodiversity-hero-him16%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eforest%20cover%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20state%20accounts%20for%2045%20percent%20compared%20to%20national%20forest%20cover%20of%20just%2021.67%20percent%20%E2%80%94%20this%20signifies%20the%20rich%20biological%20heritage%20of%20the%20state%20and%20the%20urgency%20to%20save%20one%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20largest%20carbon%20sinks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnderstanding%20the%20need%20to%20preserve%20the%20rich%20flora%20and%20fauna%20of%20the%20state%2C%20in%202022%2C%20the%20Delhi-NCR-based%20NGO%2C%20The%20Hans%20Foundation%20(THF)%20began%20community-driven%20efforts%20to%20decrease%20forest%20fires%20in%20the%20state%20and%20promote%20environmental%20conservation%20and%20ecological%20balance.%20As%20part%20of%20this%20initiative%2C%20the%20foundation%20enlisted%20volunteer%20firefighters%20%E2%80%94%20like%20Pritam%20%E2%80%94%20to%20reduce%20forest%20fire%20occurrences.%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fhans-1-1711021742.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Of%20the%20total%20forest%20cover%20of%20the%20state%2C%20more%20than%20one-third%20is%20prone%20to%20forest%20fires.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fhans-1-1711021742.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fhans-1-1711021742-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fhans-1-1711021742-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fhans-1-1711021742-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fhans-1-1711021742-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-345442%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EOf%20the%20total%20forest%20cover%20of%20the%20state%2C%20more%20than%20one-third%20is%20prone%20to%20forest%20fires.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EPreventing%20fires%20through%20community%20participation%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20THF%E2%80%99s%20intervention%2C%20Pritam%2C%20like%20many%20other%20volunteers%2C%20was%20provided%20comprehensive%20training%20to%20tackle%20forest%20fires.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20he%20was%20better%20equipped%20and%20prepared%20for%20any%20untoward%20incidents%20similar%20to%20those%20that%20occurred%20in%202022%20and%20was%20able%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20emergency%20and%20control%20potential%20fire%20incidents.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20educated%20on%20how%20to%20implement%20local%20mitigation%20strategies%20to%20effectively%20control%20any%20forest%20fire.%20We%20were%20provided%20with%20firefighting%20kits%20that%20included%20a%20set%20of%20different%20types%20of%20fire%20rakes%2C%20a%20modified%20sickle%2C%20a%20shovel%2C%20a%20fire%20beater%2C%20and%20a%20tool%20kit%20bag.%20Training%20was%20provided%20on%20fire%20line%20development%2C%20biomass%20management%2C%20safety%20measures%20during%20fire%20dousing%2C%20and%20uses%20of%20the%20various%20equipment%20that%20were%20provided%20to%20us%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExplaining%20how%20he%20responds%20to%20the%20emergency%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20first%20inform%20the%20forest%20department%20about%20any%20forest%20fires%20that%20occur%20in%20the%20area.%20Meanwhile%2C%20we%20start%20clearing%20broad%20strips%20of%20land%20of%20all%20inflammable%20material%20like%20dry%20leaves%20and%20fodder%20so%20that%20fire%20does%20not%20extend%20from%20one%20area%20to%20another.%20After%20making%20forest%20lines%2C%20we%20also%20throw%20sand%20to%20extinguish%20the%20fire.%20However%2C%20if%20the%20fire%20is%20on%20a%20large%20scale%2C%20we%20try%20to%20prevent%20it%20from%20spreading%20further%20rather%20than%20extinguishing%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2Fhans-2-1-1711021807.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3